It takes a lungeable, feeds 15,000 people.

41:05.959 --> 41:08.202
The disciples are walking around.

41:08.282 --> 41:10.446
Everybody has stuff they can't eat anymore.

41:12.028 --> 41:18.738
And it says that they walk around and they pick up 12 baskets that were parasseo.

41:19.170 --> 41:20.793
They were left over.

41:20.853 --> 41:22.495
They were a ridiculous amount.

41:22.515 --> 41:23.257
They were too much.

41:23.497 --> 41:24.619
They were hard to comprehend.

41:24.799 --> 41:25.240
Too many.

41:25.260 --> 41:26.522
They were overflowing.

41:26.722 --> 41:28.165
They abounded with food.

41:29.206 --> 41:29.907
That's the picture.

41:29.967 --> 41:32.411
That's what this word means.

41:33.052 --> 41:33.533
It's extra.

41:33.573 --> 41:34.194
It's abundant.

41:34.214 --> 41:35.737
It's overflowing.

41:35.797 --> 41:41.566
And that's the kind of hope we as the people of God have access to.

41:42.908 --> 41:46.354
And I would guess you've probably seen that at some point in your life.

41:47.266 --> 41:54.538
Like, have you ever seen somebody or do you have a friend or a parent or a grandmother that overflowed constantly with hope?

41:58.223 --> 42:02.350
I have a friend named Maya Handler is the picture of her here.

42:02.971 --> 42:15.090
When I was a student pastor of our church, Maya was 14 years old, and she was diagnosed with a very rare, aggressive and terrible form of cancer called rhabdo myosarcoma.

42:16.770 --> 42:18.553
And things, it was awful.

42:20.475 --> 42:23.780
Things accelerated seemingly overnight.

42:25.663 --> 42:27.365
And I can remember so many times.

42:27.806 --> 42:29.148
I was a young student pastor.

42:29.648 --> 42:32.432
I still don't know what I'm doing, but I really didn't know what I was doing then.

42:33.654 --> 42:39.823
I can remember pulling into the parking deck at Children's Healthcare in Atlanta, the Cancer Hospital in Atlanta.

42:40.724 --> 42:42.247
And I remember sitting in the parking deck.

42:43.008 --> 42:44.690
I would have my Bible open in my lap.

42:46.210 --> 42:49.255
tears just dripping on the pages and I would plead with God.

42:50.376 --> 42:52.359
And I would say, God, give me something.

42:53.761 --> 42:54.763
Give me a verse.

42:54.943 --> 42:55.804
Give me a prayer.

42:55.844 --> 43:00.772
Give me something that I can walk into this room and encourage this 14-year-old girl with.

43:01.793 --> 43:02.715
Just give me something.

43:04.958 --> 43:10.226
And at some point I'd close my Bible and I'd get out of the car and I'd make it up to the

43:10.562 --> 43:18.635
cancer floor at this hospital and I'd walk down the long, cold hallway into Maya's room and not one time it never failed.

43:18.655 --> 43:24.464
I would walk into her room and immediately when the door opens she would say, Grand, you're never gonna believe what I read today.

43:26.167 --> 43:27.970
You're never gonna believe this new song I heard.

43:28.711 --> 43:37.906
And then she would take out her Bible and she'd have, you know, 50 different colors circling stuff in her Bible and she was so eager to tell me about how good God was.

43:39.106 --> 43:42.511
And I remember thinking in my head, honestly, I really remember this.

43:42.551 --> 43:45.715
I was like, man, maybe she doesn't know how bad it is.

43:47.277 --> 43:49.841
Like maybe her parents just didn't tell her.

43:49.861 --> 43:55.549
Or maybe she's too young to really comprehend that she has days or weeks left.

43:58.092 --> 44:01.177
And every time I walked in, I mean ear to ear.

44:02.659 --> 44:05.042
She lost her hair and her smile got bigger.

44:06.050 --> 44:13.297
She got to a point where she couldn't stand up to go walk to the restroom anymore and the joy became more and more loud out of her room.

44:14.038 --> 44:26.209
She would have to do these MRI scans of her head and they would put her in this thing and they would ask her what music she would wanna play and she would wanna play worship music and she would insist that they turn it up as loud as it could go.

44:26.470 --> 44:29.853
And you'd be outside in the hallway and you'd hear worship music going.

44:32.035 --> 44:35.218
And I can remember thinking, walking into a room, I'd be like,

44:35.554 --> 44:38.358
I'm supposed to be here encouraging you.

44:40.501 --> 44:41.442
I'm not good at my job.

44:43.144 --> 44:44.827
I'm supposed to be in here encouraging you.

44:45.207 --> 44:46.969
I'm supposed to be transferring hope to you.

44:47.490 --> 44:50.114
And every single time I never even got a word in.

44:50.154 --> 44:56.242
And at first I thought, maybe she just doesn't understand it.

44:57.122 --> 45:00.687
And then I remember when it clicked for me, I went, oh no, I get it.

45:01.047 --> 45:16.728
She has tapped into the God of hope who has filled her with all joy and peace and believing as she trusts in him so that by the power of the Holy Spirit, even in a cancer ward, she could overflow with hope.

45:19.913 --> 45:21.134
This is the picture for us.

45:22.636 --> 45:23.858
Life is hard.

45:25.794 --> 45:27.416
But God is good.

45:28.737 --> 45:33.582
And we have a hope that Trent sends this world.

45:34.984 --> 45:46.617
Maya went home to be with Jesus and I can remember people saying to me, and they didn't mean anything by it, but I can remember people saying to me, like, I'm so sorry, you know, that it didn't work out for her.

45:46.677 --> 45:55.186
I'm so sorry that, you know, what we prayed for didn't really, and I wanted to say back to everybody lovingly, like, she got exactly what she was hoping for.

45:55.778 --> 46:23.474
not only did her hope not disappoint her hope paled in comparison when she met the one she loved most face to face and went to a place cancer can't go her hope did not get she didn't get her hopes up to be disappointed her hope will last an echo for eternity and I don't know what you're up against in life right now I don't know why

46:23.906 --> 46:26.991
Your soul feels like it's just bottoming out right now.

46:28.193 --> 46:35.425
I don't know what circumstances, I don't know what hardships, I don't know what difficulty you're facing, I don't know what kind of discouragement you're up against.

46:35.485 --> 46:38.891
I don't know what's causing you to think maybe I should just cash all this in.

46:39.151 --> 46:42.256
I don't know what lies the enemies whispering over you.

46:42.517 --> 46:45.682
I don't know what's causing you to feel hopeless.

46:47.682 --> 46:51.848
But I came here tonight to say there is a person you can put your trust in him.

46:52.108 --> 47:00.159
And as you put your trust in him, you will get a hope that is gritty and durable and dependable and will last for all of eternity.

47:00.640 --> 47:04.786
And even in the most difficult days of life, you can worship your way through.

47:05.867 --> 47:09.572
You can overflow with hope.

47:10.914 --> 47:16.562
So for the people in the room today, if you're alive in Jesus, if you belong to the King,

47:17.058 --> 47:25.848
I came on the authority of God's Word today to tell you you should get your hopes up.

47:25.868 --> 47:26.610
Let's pray together.

